reviewText: This film is so amateuristic it must have been a film school project.  The acting is so bad the producer must have given parts to his buddies instead of to qualified actors.  The woman on the cover is nowhere to be found in this film.

AFTER WATCHING THIS MOVIE  I BELIEVE IT SHOULD BE SEEN BY ANYONE WHO LOVES A GOOD ACTION AND SUSPENSE MOVIE THE STORYLINE AND ACTORS ARE GREAT LUCIFER PLAYED BY JAMES A. BASS IS FANTASTIC AND THE LEAD TILEEN IS GREAT I WOULD LOVE TO SEE A SEQUEL
